As you know, we were just able to activate the Stargate.  This portal will allow us to travel to far away lands in different solar systems.  I need you to go defeat Anubis before he comes to Earth to destroy us.

In order to succeed, you'll need to be skilled in inductive and deductive reasoning and logical fallacies.  You'll also need to work with induction and deduction in math.  If you aren't familiar with these topics, you can click Study button below to review them.  If you are, then go ahead and click Continue to go back to the game.

We will keep Anubis here once we capture him.  He is immortal so he can't be killed, but if you destroy his corporeal form, we can keep him here in stasis.

Here comes your final battle.  You won't be able to defeat the pharaohs by shooting acid at them.  But if you shoot the acid at Anubis, the pharaohs will fall.  Aim your acid at Anubis until he falls.

The following is an example of inductive or deductive reasoning

"Pharaoh is immortal. Immortals live forever. Therefore, Pharaoh will live forever."

Select the correct answer below.
I went to Cairo and the Nile was flooded. Therefore, the Nile always floods in Cairo.
I was bitten by a mosquito and now I have a fever. Therefore, I have West Nile Virus.
Pharoah must defend Egypt from foreign invaders. The engineer is a foreign invader. Therefore, Pharoah must defend Egypt from the engineer.
Frogs fell from the sky after Moses said they would.  Therefore, Moses caused the frogs to fall from the sky.
The sun rose yesterday. The sun rose today.  Therefore, the sun will rise tomorrow.
All humans are mortal.  The engineer is a man.  Therefore, the engineer is immortal.

You passed the test.  Now I will give you a gift of two new powers.

First, I will gift you with some acid from my tail. You can use this power by pressing "X" on your keyboard.  

Second, I will give you some of my hide as armor for your future battles.  This ability is automatically given, so no need to press any keys to activate it. It will show as additional hearts in your health meter.

You will need these powers in order to defeat your enemies. However, remember that acid is ineffective against enemies that themselves produce acid (scorpions and snakes).  It is also ineffective against pharaohs.
A syllogism that is not sound is inductive, not deductive.
Some pharaohs are men.  Some men are tall.  Therefore, some pharaohs are tall.

Find the logical conclusion to this syllogism:

Major Premise: All members of group A are included in group B
Minor Premise: All members of group B are included in group C
Conclusion:
All members of group B are included in group A
All members of group A are included in group C
